commit.message:
Merge pull request #5 from nikolas/patch-1

Update README.rst

Merge pull request #4 from vlad003/master

Leave units on 0 time values.

Merge pull request #1 from wtayyeb/master

Improve css compress

Leave units on 0 time values.

Browsers ignore declarations in which there is a missing unit literal after
the 0, since omitting the unit on non-length data types is considered invalid.

Merge pull request #1 from sprymix/master

merge from upstream
add tests for preserve_exclamation_comments, -/+ signs before float numbers
add preserve_exclamation_comments flag to compress more!
bump version to 0.9.3; add 'compress_partitioned' to csscompressor.__all__
Fix a bug compress_partitioned with some specific 'max_linelen' (trailing \n)
Add new function: compress_partitioned; bump version to 0.9.2

Implement support for execution from command-line

To use 'csscompressor' as a command-line tool, simply run

   $ python3 -m csscompressor --help

Support: Python 2.7 & 3.3
add MANIFEST.in to keep LICENSE in the distribution
readme: Add a note about how to run unittests
